result.execSummary:
The defendant Kelly A Karr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 3:31pm [mo]
Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for Branch IV
Defendant Kelly A Karr in court with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Ms.  Karr waives her right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds her over for Trial.
Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement given by victim, Dawn Schaller
Statement made Kelly Karr
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--the Court stays a 45 day jail term, indicating that if the Defendant fails to comply  with any of the terms of Probation, the Agent should apply to the Court for imposition of the stayed jail time. 
--to undergo assessment, treatment, or counseling the agent direct
--to maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--No possession of any personally indentifying information not in her name
--To write letter of apology to both the officer and her sister, to be submitted to her agent for approval 
--to pay costs of  $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand

Days credit for time already served:  0 days
